==English==

===Etymology===
{{OE.}} ''cropp'', head or top of a sprout or herb.

===Pronunciation===
*(''[[RP]]''): krŏp, /krɒp/, /<tt>krQp</tt>/
*(''US''): kräp, /krɑp/, /<tt>krAp</tt>/

===Noun===
'''crop''' (''plural:'' '''[[crops]]''')

#A plant grown for [[food]].
#The [[harvest]] for a particular year.
#A short [[haircut]].
#A short [[whip]] used by the rider of a horse to encourage it to run faster.
#Part of the [[alimentary tract]] of birds, insects and some other animals that is used to store food temporarily prior to [[digestion]].

====Synonyms====
*(''harvest''): [[harvest]], [[yield]]
*(''whip used on horses''): [[hunting crop]], [[riding crop]], [[whip]], [[bat]]
*(''animal's''): [[craw]] (''in birds'')

